                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 181.9202/169: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Bandholtz</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-04">October 4,
                            1919</date>.<lb/>[Received October 4—6:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>118. As a necessary step to prevent some of the suffering that is sure to ensue
                    from food and fuel shortage it is recommended that the Roumanians be obliged to
                    return immediately such portions of seized Hungary rolling stock as directed by
                    Interallied Military Mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bandholtz</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
